# Import required libraries
import pandas as pd
import numpy as np
from google.colab import files
import statsmodels.api as sm
from statsmodels.tsa.stattools import adfuller, kpss
from statsmodels.tsa.arima.model import ARIMA
from statsmodels.tsa.vector_ar.vecm import coint_johansen
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# Upload Excel files
print("Please upload MSFT Excel file")
msft_upload = files.upload()
msft_filename = list(msft_upload.keys())[0]
msft_df = pd.read_excel(msft_filename)

print("Please upload INTC Excel file")
intc_upload = files.upload()
intc_filename = list(intc_upload.keys())[0]
intc_df = pd.read_excel(intc_filename)

# Print available columns with better formatting
print("\nMSFT DataFrame columns:")
for col in msft_df.columns:
    print(f"- '{col}'")
print("\nINTC DataFrame columns:")
for col in intc_df.columns:
    print(f"- '{col}'")

# Ask user for the correct column name with guidance
print("\nNote: Enter the exact column name from above, including any spaces or case sensitivity")
close_column = input("Please enter the column name containing closing prices: ").strip()

# Verify the column exists in both DataFrames
if close_column not in msft_df.columns or close_column not in intc_df.columns:
    print(f"Error: Column '{close_column}' not found in one or both DataFrames")
    print("Available columns in MSFT:", list(msft_df.columns))
    print("Available columns in INTC:", list(intc_df.columns))
    raise KeyError(f"Column '{close_column}' not found")

# Extract closing prices using user-specified column name
try:
    msft_close = msft_df[close_column]
    intc_close = intc_df[close_column]
except KeyError as e:
    print(f"Unexpected error accessing column '{close_column}': {e}")
    raise

# Ensure both series have the same length
min_length = min(len(msft_close), len(intc_close))
msft_close = msft_close[:min_length]
intc_close = intc_close[:min_length]

# Function for unit root tests
def unit_root_tests(series, name):
    print(f"\nUnit Root Tests for {name}:")

    # ADF Test
    adf_result = adfuller(series)
    print("ADF Test:")
    print(f'ADF Statistic: {adf_result[0]:.4f}')
    print(f'p-value: {adf_result[1]:.4f}')
    print(f'Critical Values: {adf_result[4]}')

    # KPSS Test
    kpss_result = kpss(series)
    print("\nKPSS Test:")
    print(f'KPSS Statistic: {kpss_result[0]:.4f}')
    print(f'p-value: {kpss_result[1]:.4f}')
    print(f'Critical Values: {kpss_result[3]}')

# Perform unit root tests
unit_root_tests(msft_close, "MSFT")
unit_root_tests(intc_close, "INTC")

# Difference the series if non-stationary
msft_diff = msft_close.diff().dropna()
intc_diff = intc_close.diff().dropna()

# Function to find best ARMA model (using ARIMA with d=0)
def find_best_arma(series, name, max_p=3, max_q=3):
    best_aic = float('inf')
    best_order = None

    for p in range(max_p + 1):
        for q in range(max_q + 1):
            try:
                model = ARIMA(series, order=(p, 0, q))
                results = model.fit()
                if results.aic < best_aic:
                    best_aic = results.aic
                    best_order = (p, 0, q)
            except:
                continue

    print(f"\nBest ARMA model for {name}:")
    print(f"Order: {best_order}")
    print(f"AIC: {best_aic:.2f}")

    best_model = ARIMA(series, order=best_order).fit()
    return best_model

# Fit ARMA models
msft_arma = find_best_arma(msft_diff, "MSFT")
intc_arma = find_best_arma(intc_diff, "INTC")

# Cointegration test
def cointegration_test(df):
    result = coint_johansen(df, det_order=0, k_ar_diff=1)
    print("\nJohansen Cointegration Test:")
    print(f"Trace statistic: {result.lr1}")
    print(f"Critical values (90%, 95%, 99%): {result.cvt}")

    for i in range(len(result.lr1)):
        if result.lr1[i] > result.cvt[i, 1]:  # 95% critical value
            print(f"r = {i}: Cointegration exists at 95% confidence level")
        else:
            print(f"r = {i}: No cointegration at 95% confidence level")

# Prepare data for cointegration
coint_df = pd.DataFrame({
    'MSFT': msft_close,
    'INTC': intc_close
}).dropna()

# Run cointegration test
cointegration_test(coint_df)

# Plot the series
plt.figure(figsize=(12,6))
plt.plot(msft_close, label='MSFT')
plt.plot(intc_close, label='INTC')
plt.title('MSFT vs INTC Closing Prices')
plt.legend()
plt.show()

# Plot the differenced series
plt.figure(figsize=(12,6))
plt.plot(msft_diff, label='MSFT Diff')
plt.plot(intc_diff, label='INTC Diff')
plt.title('Differenced Series')
plt.legend()
plt.show()

# Import required libraries
import pandas as pd
import numpy as np
from google.colab import files
import statsmodels.api as sm
from statsmodels.tsa.stattools import adfuller, kpss
from statsmodels.tsa.arima.model import ARIMA
from statsmodels.tsa.vector_ar.vecm import coint_johansen
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# Upload Excel files
print("Please upload MSFT Excel file")
msft_upload = files.upload()
msft_filename = list(msft_upload.keys())[0]
msft_df = pd.read_excel(msft_filename)

print("Please upload GOOGL Excel file")
googl_upload = files.upload()
googl_filename = list(googl_upload.keys())[0]
googl_df = pd.read_excel(googl_filename)

# Print available columns with better formatting
print("\nMSFT DataFrame columns:")
for col in msft_df.columns:
    print(f"- '{col}'")
print("\nGOOGL DataFrame columns:")
for col in googl_df.columns:
    print(f"- '{col}'")

# Ask user for the correct column name with guidance
print("\nNote: Enter the exact column name from above, including any spaces or case sensitivity")
close_column = input("Please enter the column name containing closing prices: ").strip()

# Verify the column exists in both DataFrames
if close_column not in msft_df.columns or close_column not in googl_df.columns:
    print(f"Error: Column '{close_column}' not found in one or both DataFrames")
    print("Available columns in MSFT:", list(msft_df.columns))
    print("Available columns in GOOGL:", list(googl_df.columns))
    raise KeyError(f"Column '{close_column}' not found")

# Extract closing prices using user-specified column name
try:
    msft_close = msft_df[close_column]
    googl_close = googl_df[close_column]
except KeyError as e:
    print(f"Unexpected error accessing column '{close_column}': {e}")
    raise

# Ensure both series have the same length
min_length = min(len(msft_close), len(googl_close))
msft_close = msft_close[:min_length]
googl_close = googl_close[:min_length]

# Function for unit root tests
def unit_root_tests(series, name):
    print(f"\nUnit Root Tests for {name}:")

    # ADF Test
    adf_result = adfuller(series)
    print("ADF Test:")
    print(f'ADF Statistic: {adf_result[0]:.4f}')
    print(f'p-value: {adf_result[1]:.4f}')
    print(f'Critical Values: {adf_result[4]}')

    # KPSS Test
    kpss_result = kpss(series)
    print("\nKPSS Test:")
    print(f'KPSS Statistic: {kpss_result[0]:.4f}')
    print(f'p-value: {kpss_result[1]:.4f}')
    print(f'Critical Values: {kpss_result[3]}')

# Perform unit root tests
unit_root_tests(msft_close, "MSFT")
unit_root_tests(googl_close, "GOOGL")

# Difference the series if non-stationary
msft_diff = msft_close.diff().dropna()
googl_diff = googl_close.diff().dropna()

# Function to find best ARMA model (using ARIMA with d=0)
def find_best_arma(series, name, max_p=3, max_q=3):
    best_aic = float('inf')
    best_order = None

    for p in range(max_p + 1):
        for q in range(max_q + 1):
            try:
                model = ARIMA(series, order=(p, 0, q))
                results = model.fit()
                if results.aic < best_aic:
                    best_aic = results.aic
                    best_order = (p, 0, q)
            except:
                continue

    print(f"\nBest ARMA model for {name}:")
    print(f"Order: {best_order}")
    print(f"AIC: {best_aic:.2f}")

    best_model = ARIMA(series, order=best_order).fit()
    return best_model

# Fit ARMA models
msft_arma = find_best_arma(msft_diff, "MSFT")
googl_arma = find_best_arma(googl_diff, "GOOGL")

# Cointegration test
def cointegration_test(df):
    result = coint_johansen(df, det_order=0, k_ar_diff=1)
    print("\nJohansen Cointegration Test:")
    print(f"Trace statistic: {result.lr1}")
    print(f"Critical values (90%, 95%, 99%): {result.cvt}")

    for i in range(len(result.lr1)):
        if result.lr1[i] > result.cvt[i, 1]:  # 95% critical value
            print(f"r = {i}: Cointegration exists at 95% confidence level")
        else:
            print(f"r = {i}: No cointegration at 95% confidence level")

# Prepare data for cointegration
coint_df = pd.DataFrame({
    'MSFT': msft_close,
    'GOOGL': googl_close
}).dropna()

# Run cointegration test
cointegration_test(coint_df)

# Plot the series
plt.figure(figsize=(12,6))
plt.plot(msft_close, label='MSFT')
plt.plot(googl_close, label='GOOGL')
plt.title('MSFT vs GOOGL Closing Prices')
plt.legend()
plt.show()

# Plot the differenced series
plt.figure(figsize=(12,6))
plt.plot(msft_diff, label='MSFT Diff')
plt.plot(googl_diff, label='GOOGL Diff')
plt.title('Differenced Series')
plt.legend()
plt.show()

# Function for unit root tests
def unit_root_tests(series, name):
    print(f"\nUnit Root Tests for {name}:")

    # ADF Test
    adf_result = adfuller(series)
    print("ADF Test:")
    print(f'ADF Statistic: {adf_result[0]:.4f}')
    print(f'p-value: {adf_result[1]:.4f}')
    print(f'Critical Values: {adf_result[4]}')

    # KPSS Test
    kpss_result = kpss(series)
    print("\nKPSS Test:")
    print(f'KPSS Statistic: {kpss_result[0]:.4f}')
    print(f'p-value: {kpss_result[1]:.4f}')
    print(f'Critical Values: {kpss_result[3]}')

# Perform unit root tests
unit_root_tests(intc_close, "INTC")
unit_root_tests(googl_close, "GOOGL")

# Difference the series if non-stationary
intc_diff = intc_close.diff().dropna()
googl_diff = googl_close.diff().dropna()

# Function to find best ARMA model (using ARIMA with d=0)
def find_best_arma(series, name, max_p=3, max_q=3):
    best_aic = float('inf')
    best_order = None

    for p in range(max_p + 1):
        for q in range(max_q + 1):
            try:
                model = ARIMA(series, order=(p, 0, q))
                results = model.fit()
                if results.aic < best_aic:
                    best_aic = results.aic
                    best_order = (p, 0, q)
            except:
                continue

    print(f"\nBest ARMA model for {name}:")
    print(f"Order: {best_order}")
    print(f"AIC: {best_aic:.2f}")

    best_model = ARIMA(series, order=best_order).fit()
    return best_model

# Fit ARMA models
intc_arma = find_best_arma(intc_diff, "INTC")
googl_arma = find_best_arma(googl_diff, "GOOGL")

# Cointegration test
def cointegration_test(df):
    result = coint_johansen(df, det_order=0, k_ar_diff=1)
    print("\nJohansen Cointegration Test:")
    print(f"Trace statistic: {result.lr1}")
    print(f"Critical values (90%, 95%, 99%): {result.cvt}")

    for i in range(len(result.lr1)):
        if result.lr1[i] > result.cvt[i, 1]:  # 95% critical value
            print(f"r = {i}: Cointegration exists at 95% confidence level")
        else:
            print(f"r = {i}: No cointegration at 95% confidence level")

# Prepare data for cointegration
coint_df = pd.DataFrame({
    'INTC': intc_close,
    'GOOGL': googl_close
}).dropna()

# Run cointegration test
cointegration_test(coint_df)

import pandas as pd

from google.colab import files

from statsmodels.tsa.arima.model import ARIMA
from statsmodels.tsa.vector_ar.vecm import coint_johansen
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# Upload Excel files
print("Please upload MSFT Excel file")
msft_upload = files.upload()
msft_filename = list(msft_upload.keys())[0]
msft_df = pd.read_excel(msft_filename)

print("Please upload INTC Excel file")
intc_upload = files.upload()
intc_filename = list(intc_upload.keys())[0]
intc_df = pd.read_excel(intc_filename)

# Print available columns with better formatting
print("\nMSFT DataFrame columns:")
for col in msft_df.columns:
    print(f"- '{col}'")
print("\nINTC DataFrame columns:")
for col in intc_df.columns:
    print(f"- '{col}'")

# Ask user for the correct column name with guidance
print("\nNote: Enter the exact column name from above, including any spaces or case sensitivity")
close_column = input("Please enter the column name containing closing prices: ").strip()

# Verify the column exists in both DataFrames
if close_column not in msft_df.columns or close_column not in intc_df.columns:
    print(f"Error: Column '{close_column}' not found in one or both DataFrames")
    print("Available columns in MSFT:", list(msft_df.columns))
    print("Available columns in INTC:", list(intc_df.columns))
    raise KeyError(f"Column '{close_column}' not found")

# Extract closing prices using user-specified column name
try:
    msft_close = msft_df[close_column]
    intc_close = intc_df[close_column]
except KeyError as e:
    print(f"Unexpected error accessing column '{close_column}': {e}")
    raise

# Ensure both series have the same length
min_length = min(len(msft_close), len(intc_close))
msft_close = msft_close[:min_length]
intc_close = intc_close[:min_length]

# Function for unit root tests
def unit_root_tests(series, name):
    print(f"\nUnit Root Tests for {name}:")

    # ADF Test
    adf_result = adfuller(series)
    print("ADF Test:")
    print(f'ADF Statistic: {adf_result[0]:.4f}')
    print(f'p-value: {adf_result[1]:.4f}')
    print(f'Critical Values: {adf_result[4]}')

    # KPSS Test
    kpss_result = kpss(series)
    print("\nKPSS Test:")
    print(f'KPSS Statistic: {kpss_result[0]:.4f}')
    print(f'p-value: {kpss_result[1]:.4f}')
    print(f'Critical Values: {kpss_result[3]}')

# Perform unit root tests
unit_root_tests(msft_close, "MSFT")
unit_root_tests(intc_close, "INTC")

# Difference the series if non-stationary
msft_diff = msft_close.diff().dropna()
intc_diff = intc_close.diff().dropna()

# Function to find best ARMA model (using ARIMA with d=0)
def find_best_arma(series, name, max_p=3, max_q=3):
    best_aic = float('inf')
    best_order = None

    for p in range(max_p + 1):
        for q in range(max_q + 1):
            try:
                model = ARIMA(series, order=(p, 0, q))
                results = model.fit()
                if results.aic < best_aic:
                    best_aic = results.aic
                    best_order = (p, 0, q)
            except:
                continue

    print(f"\nBest ARMA model for {name}:")
    print(f"Order: {best_order}")
    print(f"AIC: {best_aic:.2f}")

    best_model = ARIMA(series, order=best_order).fit()
    return best_model

# Fit ARMA models
msft_arma = find_best_arma(msft_diff, "MSFT")
intc_arma = find_best_arma(intc_diff, "INTC")

# Cointegration test
def cointegration_test(df):
    result = coint_johansen(df, det_order=0, k_ar_diff=1)
    print("\nJohansen Cointegration Test:")
    print(f"Trace statistic: {result.lr1}")
    print(f"Critical values (90%, 95%, 99%): {result.cvt}")

    for i in range(len(result.lr1)):
        if result.lr1[i] > result.cvt[i, 1]:  # 95% critical value
            print(f"r = {i}: Cointegration exists at 95% confidence level")
        else:
            print(f"r = {i}: No cointegration at 95% confidence level")

# Prepare data for cointegration
coint_df = pd.DataFrame({
    'MSFT': msft_close,
    'INTC': intc_close
}).dropna()

# Run cointegration test
cointegration_test(coint_df)

# Plot the series
plt.figure(figsize=(12,6))
plt.plot(msft_close, label='MSFT')
plt.plot(intc_close, label='INTC')
plt.title('MSFT vs INTC Closing Prices')
plt.legend()
plt.show()

# Plot the differenced series
plt.figure(figsize=(12,6))
plt.plot(msft_diff, label='MSFT Diff')
plt.plot(intc_diff, label='INTC Diff')
plt.title('Differenced Series')
plt.legend()
plt.show()

# Ask user for the correct column name with guidance

close_column = input("Please enter the column name containing closing prices: ").strip()

# Verify the column exists in both DataFrames
if close_column not in msft_df.columns or close_column not in googl_df.columns:
    print(f"Error: Column '{close_column}' not found in one or both DataFrames")
    print("Available columns in MSFT:", list(msft_df.columns))
    print("Available columns in GOOGL:", list(googl_df.columns))
    raise KeyError(f"Column '{close_column}' not found")

    googl_close = googl_df[close_column]

    print(f"Unexpected error accessing column '{close_column}': {e}")

# Ensure both series have the same length
min_length = min(len(msft_close), len(googl_close))

# Function for unit root tests
def unit_root_tests(series, name):
    print(f"\nUnit Root Tests for {name}:")

    # ADF Test
    adf_result = adfuller(series)
    print("ADF Test:")
    print(f'ADF Statistic: {adf_result[0]:.4f}')
    print(f'p-value: {adf_result[1]:.4f}')
    print(f'Critical Values: {adf_result[4]}')

    # KPSS Test
    kpss_result = kpss(series)

    print(f'KPSS Statistic: {kpss_result[0]:.4f}')
    print(f'p-value: {kpss_result[1]:.4f}')
    print(f'Critical Values: {kpss_result[3]}')

unit_root_tests(googl_close, "GOOGL")

googl_diff = googl_close.diff().dropna()

# Function to find best ARMA model (using ARIMA with d=0)
def find_best_arma(series, name, max_p=3, max_q=3):
    best_aic = float('inf')
    best_order = None

    for p in range(max_p + 1):
        for q in range(max_q + 1):
            try:
                model = ARIMA(series, order=(p, 0, q))
                results = model.fit()
                if results.aic < best_aic:
                    best_aic = results.aic
                    best_order = (p, 0, q)
            except:
                continue

    print(f"\nBest ARMA model for {name}:")
    print(f"Order: {best_order}")
    print(f"AIC: {best_aic:.2f}")

    best_model = ARIMA(series, order=best_order).fit()
    return best_model

# Fit ARMA models
msft_arma = find_best_arma(msft_diff, "MSFT")
googl_arma = find_best_arma(googl_diff, "GOOGL")

# Cointegration test
def cointegration_test(df):
    result = coint_johansen(df, det_order=0, k_ar_diff=1)
    print("\nJohansen Cointegration Test:")
    print(f"Trace statistic: {result.lr1}")
    print(f"Critical values (90%, 95%, 99%): {result.cvt}")

    for i in range(len(result.lr1)):
        if result.lr1[i] > result.cvt[i, 1]:  # 95% critical value
            print(f"r = {i}: Cointegration exists at 95% confidence level")
        else:
            print(f"r = {i}: No cointegration at 95% confidence level")

# Prepare data for cointegration
coint_df = pd.DataFrame({
    'MSFT': msft_close,
    'GOOGL': googl_close
}).dropna()

# Run cointegration test
cointegration_test(coint_df)

import pandas as pd

from statsmodels.tsa.vector_ar.vecm import coint_johansen
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

# Upload Excel files
print("Please upload INTC Excel file")
intc_upload = files.upload()
intc_filename = list(intc_upload.keys())[0]
intc_df = pd.read_excel(intc_filename)

print("Please upload GOOGL Excel file")
googl_upload = files.upload()
googl_filename = list(googl_upload.keys())[0]
googl_df = pd.read_excel(googl_filename)

# Print available columns with better formatting
print("\nINTC DataFrame columns:")
for col in intc_df.columns:
    print(f"- '{col}'")
print("\nGOOGL DataFrame columns:")
for col in googl_df.columns:
    print(f"- '{col}'")

# Ask user for the correct column name with guidance
print("\nNote: Enter the exact column name from above, including any spaces or case sensitivity")
close_column = input("Please enter the column name containing closing prices: ").strip()

# Verify the column exists in both DataFrames
if close_column not in intc_df.columns or close_column not in googl_df.columns:
    print(f"Error: Column '{close_column}' not found in one or both DataFrames")
    print("Available columns in INTC:", list(intc_df.columns))
    print("Available columns in GOOGL:", list(googl_df.columns))
    raise KeyError(f"Column '{close_column}' not found")

# Extract closing prices using user-specified column name

    intc_close = intc_df[close_column]
    googl_close = googl_df[close_column]

    print(f"Unexpected error accessing column '{close_column}': {e}")
    raise

# Ensure both series have the same length
min_length = min(len(intc_close), len(googl_close))
intc_close = intc_close[:min_length]
googl_close = googl_close[:min_length]

# Function for unit root tests
def unit_root_tests(series, name):
    print(f"\nUnit Root Tests for {name}:")

    # ADF Test
    adf_result = adfuller(series)
    print("ADF Test:")
    print(f'ADF Statistic: {adf_result[0]:.4f}')
    print(f'p-value: {adf_result[1]:.4f}')
    print(f'Critical Values: {adf_result[4]}')

    # KPSS Test
    kpss_result = kpss(series)
    print("\nKPSS Test:")
    print(f'KPSS Statistic: {kpss_result[0]:.4f}')
    print(f'p-value: {kpss_result[1]:.4f}')
    print(f'Critical Values: {kpss_result[3]}')

# Perform unit root tests
unit_root_tests(intc_close, "INTC")
unit_root_tests(googl_close, "GOOGL")

# Difference the series if non-stationary
intc_diff = intc_close.diff().dropna()
googl_diff = googl_close.diff().dropna()

# Function to find best ARMA model (using ARIMA with d=0)
def find_best_arma(series, name, max_p=3, max_q=3):
    best_aic = float('inf')
    best_order = None

    for p in range(max_p + 1):
        for q in range(max_q + 1):
            try:
                model = ARIMA(series, order=(p, 0, q))
                results = model.fit()
                if results.aic < best_aic:
                    best_aic = results.aic
                    best_order = (p, 0, q)
            except:
                continue

    print(f"\nBest ARMA model for {name}:")
    print(f"Order: {best_order}")
    print(f"AIC: {best_aic:.2f}")

    best_model = ARIMA(series, order=best_order).fit()
    return best_model

# Fit ARMA models
intc_arma = find_best_arma(intc_diff, "INTC")
googl_arma = find_best_arma(googl_diff, "GOOGL")

# Cointegration test
def cointegration_test(df):
    result = coint_johansen(df, det_order=0, k_ar_diff=1)
    print("\nJohansen Cointegration Test:")
    print(f"Trace statistic: {result.lr1}")
    print(f"Critical values (90%, 95%, 99%): {result.cvt}")

    for i in range(len(result.lr1)):
        if result.lr1[i] > result.cvt[i, 1]:  # 95% critical value
            print(f"r = {i}: Cointegration exists at 95% confidence level")
        else:
            print(f"r = {i}: No cointegration at 95% confidence level")

# Prepare data for cointegration
coint_df = pd.DataFrame({
    'INTC': intc_close,
    'GOOGL': googl_close
}).dropna()

# Run cointegration test
cointegration_test(coint_df)

# Plot the series
plt.figure(figsize=(12,6))
plt.plot(intc_close, label='INTC')
plt.plot(googl_close, label='GOOGL')
plt.title('INTC vs GOOGL Closing Prices')
plt.legend()
plt.show()

# Plot the differenced series
plt.figure(figsize=(12,6))
plt.plot(intc_diff, label='INTC Diff')
plt.plot(googl_diff, label='GOOGL Diff')
plt.title('Differenced Series')
plt.legend()
plt.show()
